<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1256" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1256">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1215/417.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In pursuance of Department’s telegram of March 26, I had a conference
                            today with the President and the Minister for Foreign Affairs, both of
                            whom agreed with me that Mr. Calero should carry to Washington full
                            instructions and should immediately take up the discussion.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>